'''Congenital dyserythropoietic anemia type III''' (CDA III) is a rare autosomal dominant disorder characterized by macrocytic anemia, bone marrow erythroid hyperplasia and giant multlnucleate erythroblasts.<ref>http://hmg.oxfordjournals.org/content/4/1/109.abstract</ref>

