==Genetics==
CDA type III is transmitted autosomal dominantly. The genetic cause of CDA type III has not been identified. It likely results from mutations in a gene located on the long arm of chromosome 15 at a position designated 15q22. Researchers continue to search for the specific gene associated with this form of the condition.<ref>http://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/condition/congenital-dyserythropoietic-anemia</ref>

